,"MannorWiddington, Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom",", , , England":"England","Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Marston","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from one or other of the numerous places called Marston or Merston, in counties including Bedfordshire, Cheshire, Derbyshire, Gloucestershire, Isle of Wight, Kent, Northamptonshire, Oxfordshire, Shropshire, Staffordshire, Sussex, and Worcestershire. Most of the placenames derive from Old English <i>mersc</i> ‘marsh’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."],"variants":[{"name":"Marson","meanings":["English (Midlands): variant of   Marston  , a common placename which was often spelled and pronounced <i>Marson</i>.","French: habitational name from any of the places so called in Marne and Meuse, or from Marçon in Sarthe. This surname is also found in Germany."]},{"name":"Maston","meanings":["English: variant of   Marston   with loss of <i>-r-</i>."]}]},{"name":"Juliana","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["feminine form of <i>Julianus</i> (  see  Julian  ), which was revived in England in the 18th century and has been used occasionally ever since."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":20,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Juliana Marston was born about 1435, in Widdington, Esse